WEBVTT

00:21.089 --> 00:22.490
Hello.

00:23.657 --> 00:26.427
Oh, hello. Yes.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.696
Now? Uh, yes.

00:28.796 --> 00:30.431
Of course, of course. Absolutely.

00:30.531 --> 00:32.200
I'll be right there.

00:40.574 --> 00:42.343
Hello?

00:42.443 --> 00:43.977
What?

00:44.078 --> 00:45.613
Wait, are you serious?

00:45.713 --> 00:47.915
Uh, okay. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:51.252 --> 00:52.420
Lionel?

00:52.520 --> 00:54.922
Ah. Oh, my gosh.

00:55.022 --> 00:56.424
Okay.

00:56.524 --> 00:58.892
And, uh,
you must be Imani.

00:58.992 --> 01:00.728
Are you okay?

01:00.828 --> 01:02.296
I-I don't know.

01:02.396 --> 01:03.364
Thank you so much

01:03.464 --> 01:04.432
for coming down at this hour.

01:04.532 --> 01:06.300
Lionel, for you,
at any hour.

01:06.400 --> 01:08.669
I owe your father a lot.

01:08.769 --> 01:11.139
Are these... This is
the police report?

01:11.139 --> 01:15.309
They had my daughter
in a holding cell.

01:15.409 --> 01:17.145
She's in handcuffs.

01:17.145 --> 01:18.612
I am so sorry, but,

01:18.712 --> 01:20.981
Lionel, the charge
is attempted murder.

01:21.782 --> 01:22.883
Next.

01:22.983 --> 01:24.218
Imani, do you feel
clear-headed enough

01:24.318 --> 01:25.386
to speak on your own behalf

01:25.486 --> 01:26.887
when we go
before the judge?

01:26.987 --> 01:28.489
I think so. I-I don't know.

01:28.589 --> 01:30.158
I don't remember
any of what happened.

01:31.325 --> 01:33.461
You don't remember anything?

01:33.561 --> 01:35.396
She's a vice principal at
a grade school, for God's sakes.

01:35.496 --> 01:36.964
Josephine
is my friend.

01:37.064 --> 01:38.532
I've worked
with her for years.

01:38.632 --> 01:40.168
We-we love each other.
I-I would never...

01:40.268 --> 01:41.402
You would
never hurt her.

01:41.502 --> 01:42.736
Next case.
I understand.

01:42.836 --> 01:45.773
We're pleading not guilty.
Your Honor.

01:45.873 --> 01:47.941
They can't possibly think
she meant to kill her.

01:48.041 --> 01:50.178
This is ridiculous. And...

01:50.278 --> 01:51.579
We plead not guilty.

01:51.679 --> 01:54.348
But first we need
to argue for her release.

01:54.448 --> 01:57.185
Next case.
Okay, this next part
should be quick.

01:57.185 --> 01:58.619
Good evening, Your Honor.

01:58.719 --> 02:02.190
It's late, so let's
make this quick.

02:04.392 --> 02:06.694
Todd.

02:06.794 --> 02:08.095
Over here.

02:13.867 --> 02:15.303
Here's your
credit card back.

02:15.403 --> 02:17.004
Thank you.
I need some gum.

02:17.104 --> 02:18.672
I'm just impressed
your credit limit

02:18.772 --> 02:20.874
is high enough to
cover bail at $27,000...

02:20.974 --> 02:22.476
I don't want to
talk about it.

02:22.576 --> 02:23.977
Okay, millionaire.

02:25.779 --> 02:28.216
Look, it's nothing.
It's stupid.

02:28.216 --> 02:32.220
It was this
hospital fundraiser

02:32.220 --> 02:33.354
function thing,

02:33.454 --> 02:35.623
and I went out
after for drinks

02:35.723 --> 02:38.792
with some work people,
and it got...

02:38.892 --> 02:40.494
It got out of hand.

02:40.594 --> 02:41.595
Yeah, drunk, disorderly,

02:41.695 --> 02:42.596
resisting arrest
out of hand.

02:42.696 --> 02:43.897
Did you call Chuck?

02:43.997 --> 02:46.133
No. He's at home,
in bed, asleep.

02:46.234 --> 02:47.868
You know, I was at
home, in bed, asleep.

02:47.968 --> 02:49.570
Okay, I just don't want
anyone in the family

02:49.670 --> 02:50.804
to know that
this happened.

02:50.904 --> 02:52.039
You know,
I'm in the family.

02:52.139 --> 02:53.707
I don't want Chuck
knowing that I was...

02:53.807 --> 02:55.042
Drunk, disorderly,

02:55.142 --> 02:56.510
resisting arrest?
Yeah, I wouldn't either.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.346
Mom. Mom.

03:01.249 --> 03:03.251
Get off... Todd.

03:03.251 --> 03:05.353
Mom. Hey.

03:06.820 --> 03:09.423
I mean...
Wait, what is...

03:09.523 --> 03:10.858
Wha... What is that?

03:10.958 --> 03:12.393
Is that...

03:12.493 --> 03:14.995
Oh, no. Oh, Todd. Oh, God.
Have you been arrested?

03:15.095 --> 03:16.297
No.
What for?

03:16.397 --> 03:19.267
No, no, this is a recipe.
I bake now.

03:19.267 --> 03:20.568
Allison?

03:20.668 --> 03:22.736
Mom, hey.
I, um...

03:22.836 --> 03:24.037
Wait.

03:24.137 --> 03:25.973
Wait, Todd,
did you pull

03:26.073 --> 03:27.641
your sister out
of her fundraiser

03:27.741 --> 03:29.577
so that she could
come down here

03:29.677 --> 03:30.878
and bail you
out of jail?

03:30.978 --> 03:34.114
I... am afraid so.

03:34.282 --> 03:36.950
On her one big
night out, off work,

03:37.050 --> 03:38.286
and you...

03:38.286 --> 03:40.120
You were arrested?
What were you doing?

03:40.288 --> 03:41.989
Actually, it was, um,

03:42.089 --> 03:45.293
public disorderly... urination.

03:45.293 --> 03:47.428
Public disorderly urination?

03:47.528 --> 03:50.564
What were you doing,
peeing in every direction?

03:50.664 --> 03:51.832
Yeah, kind of. Well, I was out

03:51.932 --> 03:53.166
for a couple beers
with friends...

03:53.301 --> 03:55.303
No, Todd, no... Allison,
I am so, so sorry.

03:55.303 --> 03:56.904
Look-look what
he's done to you,

03:57.004 --> 03:58.071
you are a wreck.

03:58.171 --> 03:59.407
Wait, wait. And
were you crying?

03:59.507 --> 04:00.608
Todd.

04:00.708 --> 04:01.942
I can't even... Wait.

04:02.042 --> 04:03.677
We will talk about this,
but I have to go.

04:03.777 --> 04:05.646
Maybe you should give me
my earrings back right now. Yeah.

04:06.447 --> 04:09.182
I hope he didn't ruin
your whole night, honey.

04:11.485 --> 04:12.586
Todd.

04:14.588 --> 04:15.656
You poor, poor thing.

04:15.756 --> 04:17.224
Disorderly urination?

04:17.325 --> 04:19.159
What? I was actually ticketed
for that once in college.

04:19.327 --> 04:21.662
Oh, so you're a serial
disorderly urinator?

04:21.762 --> 04:23.163
Don't talk about my urine, okay?

04:23.331 --> 04:24.565
I just bailed you
out of jail.

04:24.665 --> 04:26.099
Yeah, with my money.

04:26.199 --> 04:27.335
Okay, let's go.

04:27.335 --> 04:30.404
Oh, I don't know
where my coat is.

04:30.504 --> 04:32.205
Or my car.

04:33.040 --> 04:34.007
Oh, no.

04:34.107 --> 04:36.610
Wow. Who are you, me?

04:39.680 --> 04:41.515
Imani, try again.

04:41.615 --> 04:43.050
Try to jog your memory.

04:43.150 --> 04:45.786
See if you can recall anything.

04:45.886 --> 04:47.955
I don't...

04:48.055 --> 04:50.190
The cake.

04:50.958 --> 04:52.092
I opened the box.

04:52.192 --> 04:54.261
I think I put
a candle on it?

04:54.362 --> 04:56.430
Mm-hmm.
Maybe not.

04:56.530 --> 04:57.865
I remember...

04:57.965 --> 04:59.066
it was Josephine's birthday,

04:59.166 --> 05:01.134
and we were going to sing

05:01.234 --> 05:02.603
in the teacher's lounge,

05:02.703 --> 05:04.538
and then...

05:06.006 --> 05:07.741
And then...

05:07.841 --> 05:09.677
Nothing.

05:09.777 --> 05:11.945
Until...

05:12.045 --> 05:13.881
the screaming.

05:13.981 --> 05:15.383
The police
were there,

05:15.383 --> 05:19.019
and I had her blood...

05:19.119 --> 05:20.554
on my hand.

05:20.654 --> 05:23.123
I'm still not even sure
what really happened.

05:23.223 --> 05:26.093
Well, three eye-witnesses say

05:26.193 --> 05:27.628
that you took the cake knife

05:27.728 --> 05:30.664
and plunged it into
Josephine Velez's shoulder,

05:30.764 --> 05:33.467
and that if she hadn't
moved at the last second,

05:33.567 --> 05:35.769
it could have
gone into her heart.

05:36.770 --> 05:38.038
You're both
very lucky

05:38.138 --> 05:39.773
it wasn't much worse.

05:39.873 --> 05:42.009
That night,
after court,

05:42.109 --> 05:45.579
driving me home, my dad...

05:45.679 --> 05:46.947
he was scared of me.

05:47.047 --> 05:48.782
I could tell.

05:48.882 --> 05:50.317
It's so weird.

05:51.419 --> 05:53.454
We've always been so close, and

05:53.554 --> 05:56.323
now he's
afraid of me.

05:56.424 --> 05:58.726
And I'm afraid, too.

06:02.062 --> 06:04.231
What's wrong with me?

06:05.032 --> 06:06.834
I don't know,

06:06.934 --> 06:08.669
but we are going to find out.

06:10.938 --> 06:13.841
And, Imani, I'm not afraid.

06:13.941 --> 06:16.076
<i>You know, Todd,</i>

06:16.176 --> 06:17.645
I just don't
understand.

06:17.745 --> 06:19.580
You have been
doing so well.

06:19.680 --> 06:20.948
Uh, where are
the teachers?

06:21.048 --> 06:21.949
Why aren't they lounging?

06:22.049 --> 06:22.950
Because they
are teaching.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.251
We're early.

06:24.351 --> 06:25.886
Todd, you've been
putting in all those hours

06:25.986 --> 06:27.154
to get your license back,

06:27.254 --> 06:28.789
and then,
all of a sudden,

06:28.889 --> 06:31.191
you are talking to Veronica.

06:31.291 --> 06:33.126
And you got arrested. Again.

06:33.226 --> 06:37.097
I am a great disappointment,
and mystery, even to myself.

06:37.197 --> 06:39.467
Todd, you are backsliding.

06:39.467 --> 06:41.835
What do you think about therapy?

06:41.935 --> 06:43.537
Or a life coach?

06:43.637 --> 06:44.505
Teachers?

06:44.605 --> 06:46.106
Teachers, if you
can hear me,

06:46.206 --> 06:47.475
please show up. Please.

06:47.575 --> 06:49.610
Calling Allison
to bail you out.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.912
Did you really think that
I wouldn't find out?

06:52.012 --> 06:53.313
Sort of?

06:53.481 --> 06:55.148
Todd, I find
out everything.
I know that...

06:55.248 --> 06:57.250
Excuse me, can I help you two?

06:57.350 --> 07:00.521
Yes, apparently
I need a lot of it.

07:00.621 --> 07:02.222
I was standing right there.

07:02.322 --> 07:04.291
Yes...
I mean, I was
right there.

07:04.391 --> 07:06.727
I had the cake plates,
and she just...

07:06.827 --> 07:08.662
I understand, yes.
But did you know...

07:08.762 --> 07:11.298
She could have stabbed me.
I could have gotten stabbed.

07:11.398 --> 07:12.833
But she stabbed
the principal, Ms. Velez.

07:12.933 --> 07:15.969
Yes. Yes, well,
Imani was probably still upset.

07:16.069 --> 07:17.170
I mean, obviously.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.072
She stabbed her.

07:19.172 --> 07:20.708
Upset? About what?

07:20.808 --> 07:23.110
Well, Imani wanted
the principal job,

07:23.210 --> 07:24.311
but Josephine got it.

07:24.411 --> 07:26.914
They used to be real close.

07:27.014 --> 07:29.382
So they had a falling out?
Oh, I don't know.

07:29.517 --> 07:32.185
I mean, I didn't think
she was that upset.

07:32.285 --> 07:33.654
But she did stab her.

07:33.754 --> 07:35.388
Wait, so did she stab her or...

07:35.523 --> 07:36.657
Over a promotion?

07:36.757 --> 07:38.125
I mean, who wouldn't want
to be principal?

07:38.225 --> 07:41.529
I would, but I wouldn't
stab anyone to get it.

07:41.629 --> 07:43.263
And neither would Imani.

07:43.363 --> 07:45.766
And yet... she did.
She stabbed her.

07:45.866 --> 07:47.535
You know, I'm starting to think

07:47.635 --> 07:49.302
someone might have stabbed
someone in this situation.

07:49.402 --> 07:50.804
So she never said
anything to you

07:50.904 --> 07:53.340
about wanting to cause
real harm to Ms. Velez,

07:53.440 --> 07:54.775
or remove her from her job?

07:54.875 --> 07:56.443
Or the planet?

07:56.544 --> 07:57.845
Look, all I know is
we were singing

07:57.945 --> 07:59.947
"Happy Birthday" to
Josephine, and then...

08:00.047 --> 08:01.248
She stabbed her. Yeah.

08:01.348 --> 08:02.550
None of it
makes any sense.

08:02.550 --> 08:03.884
But the video doesn't lie.

08:03.984 --> 08:05.452
The video?

08:06.620 --> 08:08.556
Happy birthday.
Happy birthday.

08:10.057 --> 08:12.459
Thank you, everyone.
Thank you. Thank you.

08:13.594 --> 08:15.863
This is actually
quite suspenseful.

08:15.963 --> 08:17.598
It's like a found footage
horror movie.

08:17.698 --> 08:19.833
It's like
<i>The Blair Wits Process.</i>

08:19.933 --> 08:20.868
Those poor kids.

08:20.968 --> 08:22.770
<i>Blair Witch Project,</i> Mom.

08:22.870 --> 08:24.237
And that movie wasn't real.

08:24.337 --> 08:26.439
I am talking about the children

08:26.574 --> 08:27.975
you made me drag
to see that movie

08:28.075 --> 08:29.176
for your eighth birthday.

08:29.276 --> 08:32.145
13 hysterical boys.

08:32.245 --> 08:33.346
Half wet their pants.

08:33.446 --> 08:35.182
And, uh, who was
actually filming this?

08:35.282 --> 08:38.151
This is Horatio Menendez,
the Spanish teacher.

08:38.251 --> 08:39.452
This is his phone.

08:39.587 --> 08:41.354
And there's Imani
with the cake.

08:41.454 --> 08:44.592
And that is the victim. Principal
Josephine Velez.

08:44.592 --> 08:47.327
Mm-hmm.
Mm. This is tricky.

08:47.427 --> 08:48.762
How do you build a defense

08:48.862 --> 08:50.263
when they have actual
footage of the crime?

08:50.363 --> 08:52.900
We do not
have legitimate motive.

08:53.000 --> 08:54.802
Imani has no
criminal history,

08:54.902 --> 08:57.237
and she is a dedicated teacher. Wait,
wait, wait.

08:57.337 --> 08:59.272
Look over there, by the table.

08:59.372 --> 09:02.610
She just
sort of slumped.

09:03.611 --> 09:04.612
Wait.

09:04.712 --> 09:06.346
Is her hand

09:06.446 --> 09:07.648
shaking slightly?

09:07.748 --> 09:08.949
Look at that.

09:09.049 --> 09:11.852
This is so amazingly scary.

09:12.720 --> 09:14.454
And her eyes look odd.

09:14.622 --> 09:17.725
Glassy. Yes.

09:17.825 --> 09:19.192
There is something
not right with her.

09:19.292 --> 09:20.694
Those are tremors.
I'm certain of it.

09:20.794 --> 09:22.295
No really. Imani, I'm fine.

09:22.395 --> 09:25.332
Oh, she's-she's got the knife.
Oh, God. Oh, God.

09:25.432 --> 09:27.801
Oh, my God!

09:27.901 --> 09:30.037
We all need to show this
video to three other people

09:30.137 --> 09:32.072
so she doesn't climb
out here and kill us.

09:32.172 --> 09:35.142
We need to have Imani
examined by a doctor.

09:35.242 --> 09:37.110
And you as well.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.086
Thank you so much for
fitting Imani in today.

09:46.186 --> 09:48.321
Sure. I mean,
the ER lab is fast,

09:48.421 --> 09:49.522
but this is gonna be expensive.

09:49.657 --> 09:50.858
Oh, her father
can afford it.

09:50.958 --> 09:51.659
Oh.
He owns
Wieden Kennedy,

09:51.759 --> 09:53.927
the ad agency.

09:54.027 --> 09:55.462
He was the first
big client

09:55.562 --> 09:56.830
that I pulled in.
Mm-hmm.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.666
And Imani
is his prized

09:58.666 --> 09:59.833
and cherished daughter,

09:59.933 --> 10:02.703
just like
you are mine.

10:03.704 --> 10:05.138
Mom, I, um...

10:05.238 --> 10:07.741
Oh, I know. Todd.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.042
I cannot believe

10:09.142 --> 10:10.410
that you had to bail
him out last night.

10:10.510 --> 10:12.045
I am so sorry, Allison.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.814
And he ruined your
fun night out. You...

10:13.914 --> 10:16.283
I didn't bail him out,
he bailed me out.

10:16.383 --> 10:17.785
I was arrested

10:17.885 --> 10:19.753
for public disorderly conduct.

10:19.853 --> 10:21.655
Wha...
Dr. Grant?

10:21.755 --> 10:22.790
Hi.
The neuro consult

10:22.890 --> 10:24.191
says there's
nothing abnormal.

10:24.291 --> 10:27.494
So that rules out seizures
caused by brain tumors.

10:27.594 --> 10:29.596
I'm sorry, you were arrested?

10:29.697 --> 10:31.665
Okay. So, and also,
her bloodwork,

10:31.765 --> 10:34.367
EKG and angiogram all
confirm no heart issues.

10:34.467 --> 10:36.303
I did notice
she's been taking Orcholax,

10:36.403 --> 10:38.305
a cholesterol drug,
for about 6 months.

10:38.405 --> 10:39.807
Okay.

10:39.907 --> 10:42.609
And her bloodwork shows
drastically elevated CK

10:42.710 --> 10:44.477
between then and now.

10:44.577 --> 10:45.946
That could be
the Orcholax.

10:46.046 --> 10:47.347
There's no known listed
side effects online,

10:47.447 --> 10:49.349
but it might be worth
talking to a specialist.

10:49.449 --> 10:52.252
Wonderful. Do you know
of anyone in that field?

10:52.352 --> 10:54.621
Actually, yes.
Dr. Newton Featherstone.

10:54.722 --> 10:56.556
Okay.
Thanks.

10:56.656 --> 10:58.591
WOMAN (over P.A.):
Paging Dr. Grant
to trauma room four.

10:58.692 --> 11:01.328
Dr. Grant to trauma room four.
Sorry, Mom,
a trauma's come in, so...

11:01.428 --> 11:03.463
What? Wait, Allison,
you cannot just tell me

11:03.563 --> 11:06.066
that you were arrested,
and then flee like a criminal.

11:06.166 --> 11:07.134
I'm not fleeing like a criminal,

11:07.234 --> 11:08.535
I'm being called to save a life,

11:08.635 --> 11:10.070
like a doctor.
Okay, but

11:10.170 --> 11:12.039
we will deal with this. Yup.

11:13.440 --> 11:14.641
You lied to me.

11:14.742 --> 11:15.943
Uh, which lie are
we talking about?

11:16.043 --> 11:18.779
You weren't arrested.
Ah. Yes. Okay.

11:18.879 --> 11:19.980
But that's a good
thing, though, right?

11:20.080 --> 11:21.314
For me? I'm
the good one here.

11:21.414 --> 11:22.315
I was helping her.

11:22.415 --> 11:24.251
No. Good morning, Yu Jin.

11:24.351 --> 11:27.454
You lied about lying.
That's a double lie.

11:27.554 --> 11:28.655
Colluding with
your sister.

11:28.756 --> 11:29.923
Collu...
I wasn't collu...

11:30.023 --> 11:32.025
Again, me good,
her bad.

11:32.125 --> 11:34.594
Both of you.
Lying. To my face.

11:34.762 --> 11:35.963
Your mother.

11:36.063 --> 11:38.598
Oh, Allison.
Good God.

11:38.766 --> 11:40.768
What is going
on with her?

11:40.768 --> 11:42.035
Right, that's right,
she's the one

11:42.135 --> 11:43.536
in trouble here,
because I was just...

11:43.636 --> 11:45.005
Leading her down a path.

11:45.105 --> 11:46.874
I wasn't leading her
down any paths.

11:46.974 --> 11:48.241
This was her.
Believe me,

11:48.341 --> 11:50.443
I was just as shocked
as you. Shocked.

11:50.543 --> 11:52.645
What is happening with her?

11:52.780 --> 11:54.647
Is her life
falling apart?

11:54.782 --> 11:56.383
I don't expect
this kind of thing

11:56.483 --> 11:58.351
from Allison.

11:58.451 --> 11:59.486
What if she loses

11:59.586 --> 12:01.889
her medical license? Or her job?

12:01.989 --> 12:04.925
Wow... This is what it's like.

12:05.025 --> 12:06.359
To be the child complained to,

12:06.459 --> 12:08.028
and not the child
complained about.

12:08.128 --> 12:10.130
It's not
a competition, Todd.
No, no, no, no,

12:10.230 --> 12:11.498
I'm not competing,
I'm just saying,

12:11.598 --> 12:14.234
she's in trouble
and I'm giving you advice.

12:14.334 --> 12:16.303
It's like
I'm the responsible one.

