Just click that
button right there.

25:11.744 --> 25:12.745
Click it. Great, sent.

25:12.845 --> 25:14.046
Wonderful.
We've done it.

25:14.146 --> 25:15.281
Okay, everybody,

25:15.381 --> 25:16.282
thank you all for attending,

25:16.382 --> 25:17.349
and let's give Gavin

25:17.449 --> 25:19.051
a big round of applause, okay?

25:19.151 --> 25:21.087
Oh! Oh!

25:22.254 --> 25:23.990
Hi.

25:30.597 --> 25:31.698
Your Honor, this video
conclusively proves

25:31.798 --> 25:33.600
that Imani's actions
were a direct result

25:33.600 --> 25:34.867
of the drug
she was on.

25:34.967 --> 25:36.869
She can't
introduce this.

25:36.969 --> 25:38.605
This research was
stolen yesterday

25:38.605 --> 25:39.772
by someone masquerading

25:39.872 --> 25:41.407
as a drug
trial patient.

25:41.507 --> 25:42.809
Someone who fits
the description

25:42.909 --> 25:46.245
of Ms. Wright's son
Todd precisely.

25:46.345 --> 25:47.814
Is this true?

25:47.914 --> 25:49.882
That seems totally out of
character for you, Ms. Wright.

25:49.982 --> 25:51.150
Your Honor,

25:51.250 --> 25:52.619
in <i>Van Buskirk
vs. Amon,</i> 2007,

25:52.719 --> 25:54.854
you ruled that
a private journal

25:54.954 --> 25:56.723
stolen by
a housekeeper

25:56.823 --> 25:57.957
could be used
as evidence

25:58.057 --> 25:59.258
in a murder trial.

25:59.358 --> 26:00.827
Your client stabbed Josephine...

26:00.927 --> 26:03.295
Because Volthrupp covered
up the side effects,

26:03.395 --> 26:04.997
the dangerous side
effects, of the drug.

26:05.097 --> 26:07.299
Your Honor, what
if other people

26:07.399 --> 26:08.801
out there have taken this,

26:08.901 --> 26:11.638
and they've hurt themselves,
or... or loved ones?

26:11.638 --> 26:13.505
For health and safety
of the public,

26:13.640 --> 26:16.075
we cannot allow
big drug companies

26:16.175 --> 26:18.645
to bury the results
of their research for profit.

26:18.645 --> 26:20.279
I'm sorry.

26:20.379 --> 26:22.782
Motion to suppress granted.

26:30.089 --> 26:32.825
Stop using
my email addresses.

26:32.925 --> 26:34.661
What are you talking about?

26:34.661 --> 26:35.728
You gave my email to some
"Netty Carbine"

26:35.828 --> 26:36.996
at the Portland Computer Source,

26:37.096 --> 26:38.530
and now she's reaching
out to connect with

26:38.665 --> 26:40.199
"the young man
with the floppy hands."

26:40.299 --> 26:41.500
What does that
even mean?

26:41.668 --> 26:43.102
Oh, she must have seen me
onstage at the...

26:43.202 --> 26:45.437
Wait, what did you say
her name was again?

26:45.537 --> 26:46.673
Netty Carbine.

26:46.673 --> 26:49.408
I saw your demo
at the computer shop.

26:49.508 --> 26:50.843
Your hands got better?

26:50.943 --> 26:53.412
Oh, yes, all better.
Uh, thank you.

26:53.512 --> 26:54.981
So, how can we help you?

26:55.081 --> 26:56.783
Well, when I saw
that video the other day,

26:56.883 --> 26:58.150
I couldn't believe it.

26:58.250 --> 26:59.952
I mean, those people
looked exactly like

27:00.052 --> 27:02.689
my sister LuAnn before she died.

27:03.555 --> 27:05.291
And, uh, how did she die?

27:05.391 --> 27:07.426
She drove off a cliff.

27:07.526 --> 27:10.797
My God. I'm-I'm so sorry.

27:10.897 --> 27:13.833
But it was the tremors
and the glazed eyes.

27:13.933 --> 27:15.768
I mean, she had
that look exactly.

27:15.868 --> 27:19.071
I thought that
if you had that video,

27:19.171 --> 27:22.709
then maybe you might know
what really happened with her.

27:22.709 --> 27:25.011
And was your sister,
by any chance,

27:25.111 --> 27:27.246
taking a drug called Orcholax?

27:27.346 --> 27:28.848
I don't know.

27:28.948 --> 27:33.352
But I do have her papers
and her records in my garage.

27:33.452 --> 27:34.721
I-I could look at them,

27:34.721 --> 27:36.723
and, uh, maybe
tomorrow, I could...

27:36.723 --> 27:38.725
How-how about
tonight?

27:38.725 --> 27:39.859
We could
drive you home

27:39.959 --> 27:41.027
and we could
look together.

27:41.127 --> 27:43.796
Okay. I don't know what's there,

27:43.896 --> 27:45.898
but sure, why not?

27:45.998 --> 27:48.901
I live in a garage,
so we're good.

27:51.337 --> 27:55.074
Okay, I've got this in order,
and the condition of release.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.343
All right, uh, have you written
the letter to the judge?

27:57.443 --> 27:58.778
Yeah, I did.

27:58.878 --> 28:00.146
Okay, great. Do you want to, um,

28:00.246 --> 28:02.448
do you want to practice it?

28:06.585 --> 28:10.122
"Your Honor,
I've never done anything wrong.

28:10.222 --> 28:13.359
"Never acted out,
never broke curfew,

28:13.459 --> 28:14.794
"never did drugs,

28:14.894 --> 28:17.864
"never dated a boy
my parents didn't like. Never.

28:17.964 --> 28:19.799
"The other
night, I did

28:19.899 --> 28:21.567
"a few things
wrong in a row.

28:21.667 --> 28:24.236
"I am sorry I broke a window
and a policeman's nose.

28:24.336 --> 28:26.773
"But, otherwise,

28:26.773 --> 28:28.307
"I'm not really sorry.

28:28.407 --> 28:30.442
"I'm not sorry
I went a little crazy.

28:30.542 --> 28:32.111
"I'm not sorry
I broke the rules.

28:32.211 --> 28:34.013
"Because, after
a lifetime of doing

28:34.113 --> 28:35.681
"what everyone else
wanted me to do,

28:35.782 --> 28:37.049
"getting all
the way

28:37.149 --> 28:39.651
"to age 34 without
acting out,

28:39.786 --> 28:41.020
"maybe I should be

28:41.120 --> 28:42.989
"celebrated instead of punished.

28:43.089 --> 28:44.991
"Maybe we should have
a little party.

28:45.091 --> 28:46.793
"Sincerely,

28:46.793 --> 28:49.862
Dr. Allison
Eleanor Wright Grant."

28:51.697 --> 28:54.633
Great. You think the judge
will go for that?

28:54.801 --> 28:57.169
I hope so.

28:58.604 --> 29:01.073
I don't even know
who you are anymore.

29:01.173 --> 29:02.875
Welcome to the club.

29:02.975 --> 29:05.511
I mean, how-how-how do you
expect me to help you, Allison?

29:05.611 --> 29:07.814
I actually didn't ask
for you to help me.

29:07.814 --> 29:09.715
Are you-- are you this unhappy,

29:09.816 --> 29:11.918
that you're just gonna
sabotage everything?

29:12.018 --> 29:14.653
Do you want to leave Chuck?
Do you want to lose your job?

29:14.821 --> 29:16.522
Do you want
to go to jail?

29:16.622 --> 29:17.656
No, and yes.

29:17.824 --> 29:19.191
I mean, it-it changes.

29:19.291 --> 29:20.893
It... No,
I'm happy.

29:20.993 --> 29:22.528
I'm happy like
you and Dad were happy.

29:22.628 --> 29:24.831
I don't want to talk about that,
that is very complicated...

29:24.831 --> 29:26.065
Like you and Harry were happy.

29:26.165 --> 29:28.167
Allison.

29:28.267 --> 29:29.969
You're conflating something.

29:30.069 --> 29:31.470
Harry was a weak man.

29:31.570 --> 29:33.205
He was a weak man
who did not know

29:33.305 --> 29:35.507
how to step up to the plate
and actually be a man.

29:35.607 --> 29:38.277
And-and you are
going to tell me,

29:38.377 --> 29:40.379
blame me, and tell me that

29:40.479 --> 29:42.148
that, somehow,
has something to do with,

29:42.248 --> 29:43.749
with this particular
life moment of yours?

29:43.850 --> 29:46.085
No, you're right, Mom,
because you're always right,

29:46.185 --> 29:48.720
and there's no point
in arguing with you, okay?

29:48.855 --> 29:50.522
This is on me. I did it.

29:50.622 --> 29:53.359
I snapped,
just like your client.

29:53.459 --> 29:54.760
Just like Harry,

29:54.861 --> 29:56.963
and maybe I'm the next one
to flee to Iceland.

29:57.063 --> 29:59.231
Allison, please,
you're not fleeing anywhere.

29:59.331 --> 30:00.867
Don't worry, Mom,
I will see you

30:00.867 --> 30:02.134
in court before then.

30:02.234 --> 30:04.170
Oh, wait. Wait, Allison, honey.

30:04.270 --> 30:05.437
Don't forget your letter.

30:05.537 --> 30:07.106
Don't forget this great,
wonderful letter.

30:11.043 --> 30:12.444
Ugh, voice mail.

30:12.544 --> 30:14.146
Hey, Susan, look,

30:14.246 --> 30:16.916
I know that the info
we scored at Netty's garage

30:17.016 --> 30:18.350
was a big win.

30:18.450 --> 30:20.586
I mean, her sister was
a part of the original

30:20.686 --> 30:22.088
Orcholax drug trials,

30:22.188 --> 30:24.623
but it was initially developed
by a Dr. Norman Smith.

30:24.723 --> 30:26.959
He just used his credit card
here, like, an hour ago.

30:27.059 --> 30:28.594
Only thing is, nobody looks like

30:28.694 --> 30:30.396
an important
doctor person, so...

30:30.496 --> 30:33.132
I will keep you posted,
okay? Bye.

30:34.500 --> 30:35.767
Um...

30:36.969 --> 30:38.370
Excuse me? Hi?

30:38.470 --> 30:39.505
Hi.

30:40.472 --> 30:43.309
That's on tap, right? Cool.

30:43.409 --> 30:44.977
Um...

30:45.077 --> 30:47.646
Hi, there. Can you just, um...

30:47.746 --> 30:49.148
Oop, selfie.

30:58.457 --> 30:59.225
Norman?

30:59.325 --> 31:01.160
Hmm?
Doctor?

31:01.994 --> 31:03.930
Ah.

31:03.930 --> 31:04.931
Hey.

31:04.931 --> 31:06.498
Get me

31:06.598 --> 31:10.736
a Harvey Wallbanger, will you?

31:11.837 --> 31:13.539
Coming right up.

31:18.510 --> 31:20.546
Hello.
Yeah, he'll be fine.

31:20.646 --> 31:21.948
Think something's
going around.

31:22.048 --> 31:23.082
You guys should
get out of here.

31:23.182 --> 31:24.750
Okay, stop.

31:24.850 --> 31:25.985
Turn around.
What?

31:26.085 --> 31:27.386
Coffee.

31:27.486 --> 31:29.755
We'll need
lots of coffee. Okay.

31:29.855 --> 31:32.191
Orcholax was my project.

31:32.291 --> 31:34.026
And what happened?

31:34.126 --> 31:36.295
All the early trials
were on target.

31:36.395 --> 31:37.763
Excitement in the company

31:37.863 --> 31:39.398
was through the roof,
and then...

31:39.498 --> 31:41.467
You turned up problems.

31:41.567 --> 31:43.535
A neuro ADR side effect

31:43.635 --> 31:46.805
that could cause
a dissociative blackout

31:46.973 --> 31:49.808
in a... in a rare

31:49.976 --> 31:51.377
subset of participants.

31:51.477 --> 31:54.981
The risk was tiny,
but it existed.

31:54.981 --> 31:56.548
I asked for
another trial

31:56.648 --> 31:59.151
before we took the drug
to FDA, but, uh...

31:59.251 --> 32:01.520
But Volthrupp didn't want
that to happen.

32:02.989 --> 32:06.192
They decided
the risks were "acceptable."

32:07.593 --> 32:11.463
Dr. Smith, my client is
one of that rare subset,

32:11.563 --> 32:14.333
and she is now on trial
for attempted murder.

32:14.433 --> 32:17.469
Would you consider
testifying tomorrow...

32:17.569 --> 32:19.205
I-I signed an NDA.

32:19.305 --> 32:21.540
I shouldn't even
be talking to you.

32:21.640 --> 32:24.376
A court cannot enforce an NDA
if it violates state law.

32:24.476 --> 32:26.845
If Volthrupp is
knowingly selling drugs

32:27.013 --> 32:28.547
with adverse effects

32:28.647 --> 32:31.083
without disclosing
them to the public,

32:31.183 --> 32:33.319
you're safe.

32:34.420 --> 32:38.224
Dr. Smith, please come
to court tomorrow,

32:38.324 --> 32:40.026
sober,

32:40.026 --> 32:42.461
and testify on our behalf.

32:46.132 --> 32:47.366
Okay.

32:47.466 --> 32:49.668
Excellent.

32:51.403 --> 32:52.571
Todd, period.

32:52.671 --> 32:56.075
Court starts
in three minutes, period.

32:56.175 --> 32:57.876
Where are you, question mark?

32:58.044 --> 32:59.478
This cannot be...

32:59.578 --> 33:01.047
Wait, what happened?

33:01.147 --> 33:03.082
I'm gonna say about a half
a fifth of vodka happened.

33:03.182 --> 33:04.550
Oh!
I ran him through a
shower, poured some coffee

33:04.650 --> 33:06.652
down his throat.
I mean, what do we do?

33:06.752 --> 33:07.886
Boatman.

33:08.054 --> 33:09.855
Margaret.

33:09.955 --> 33:12.358
We proceed.

33:13.925 --> 33:16.628
And you identified a set
of neuro ADR side effects,

33:16.728 --> 33:18.097
is that correct,
Dr. Smith?

33:18.197 --> 33:19.831
Yup.

33:21.067 --> 33:22.068
And-and what

33:22.168 --> 33:24.070
were the effects caused by these

33:24.170 --> 33:26.938
adverse drug reactions
in a subset of participants?

33:27.073 --> 33:28.507
They blacked out.

33:28.607 --> 33:30.442
Yes, blackout. Um, and-and

33:30.542 --> 33:32.911
did any of the participants

33:33.079 --> 33:36.182
have violent episodes
during their blackouts?

33:36.282 --> 33:37.883
Oh, yeah.
One of them

33:37.983 --> 33:39.085
came after me with a...

33:39.085 --> 33:42.488
What's... What's it,
when stab... mail...

33:42.588 --> 33:44.523
Uh, uh, a letter opener?

33:44.623 --> 33:46.992
That's the one. Ha, ha.

33:48.260 --> 33:51.097
So, one of your patients,

33:51.097 --> 33:53.332
in a dissociative blackout,

33:53.432 --> 33:55.234
took a letter opener--

33:55.334 --> 33:59.238
which is in the shape of a
knife-- and used it as a weapon

33:59.338 --> 34:01.107
to harm you, correct?

34:01.207 --> 34:04.343
But they were real sorry after.

34:04.443 --> 34:06.445
They didn't even know.

34:07.246 --> 34:08.514
Ah.

34:08.614 --> 34:10.816
They didn't even know.

34:14.586 --> 34:16.122
Your witness.

34:17.556 --> 34:20.126
Mr. Smith, you...
It's Dr. Smith.

34:20.126 --> 34:21.960
Noted.

34:22.128 --> 34:24.863
Dr. Smith, you were fired
from Volthrupp

34:24.963 --> 34:26.732
in the middle of Orcholax's
test phases, weren't you?

34:26.832 --> 34:30.136
Yup. Right in the middle.

34:30.236 --> 34:32.037
And you were fired
from lots of other jobs

34:32.138 --> 34:33.472
after that, weren't you?

34:33.572 --> 34:35.541
Objection.
Relevance.

34:35.641 --> 34:36.742
Well, this gentleman
is being offered

34:36.842 --> 34:39.010
as an expert
in his field, Your Honor.

34:39.145 --> 34:40.479
Overruled.

34:40.579 --> 34:43.715
Mostly, I was fired

34:43.815 --> 34:47.519
'cause the companies
wanted the big money,

34:47.619 --> 34:49.155
not the truth.

34:49.155 --> 34:50.956
Wouldn't you say you were
fired because you're a drunk?

34:51.056 --> 34:52.958
Objection.
Inflammatory.

34:53.058 --> 34:56.595
Would you submit to a blood
alcohol level test, right now?

34:56.695 --> 34:58.530
Dr. Smith is not
on trial here.

34:58.630 --> 35:00.432
The man, the doctor,

35:00.532 --> 35:02.368
is flat out drunk
on the witness stand.

35:02.468 --> 35:05.337
I submit that Dr. Smith
has been fully impeached,

35:05.437 --> 35:06.772
and as such, his testimony

35:06.872 --> 35:07.839
should be stricken
from the record.

35:07.939 --> 35:09.408
Well, just because

35:09.508 --> 35:11.777
he's a little
bit impaired...
A little bit?

35:12.711 --> 35:15.347
I'm inclined to side
with Mr. Boatman.

35:15.447 --> 35:16.848
Uh, uh, redirect, Your Honor,

35:16.948 --> 35:19.251
before you make that decision?

35:26.325 --> 35:28.727
Dr. Smith,

35:28.827 --> 35:30.296
when did you start drinking?

35:30.396 --> 35:32.264
6:30 this morning.

35:34.600 --> 35:36.235
No,

35:36.335 --> 35:38.937
I meant... in your life.

35:39.037 --> 35:42.040
When did you start
drinking in your life?

35:46.212 --> 35:47.913
When Volthrupp

35:48.013 --> 35:50.916
started suppressing my results.

35:52.050 --> 35:53.118
Uh-huh.

35:53.219 --> 35:57.956
And what did
Volthrupp do to you?

35:58.056 --> 35:59.625
Pushed me
to do the opposite

35:59.725 --> 36:02.594
of what a doctor's
supposed to do.

36:02.694 --> 36:04.396
Hide results,

36:04.496 --> 36:06.598
and hurt people.

36:06.698 --> 36:08.600
When I said, "No..."

36:10.236 --> 36:11.903
...they fired me.

36:12.003 --> 36:14.506
They fired you.

36:14.606 --> 36:17.075
And how did that make you feel?

36:17.243 --> 36:18.744
I'm, uh...

36:18.844 --> 36:21.079
I'm sad.

36:23.349 --> 36:25.251
I failed people.

36:26.017 --> 36:29.388
Bad things were gonna happen
'cause of my drug...

36:30.489 --> 36:34.360
...and they wouldn't
let me tell anybody.

36:39.931 --> 36:42.701
Dr. Smith's testimony stays in.

36:45.871 --> 36:47.973
The defense rests.

36:50.041 --> 36:51.109
<i>In the matter of the attempted</i>

36:51.277 --> 36:53.279
murder of
Josephine Velez...

36:54.613 --> 36:57.082
...how does
the jury find?

36:58.149 --> 37:01.487
We find
the defendant...

37:01.587 --> 37:02.821
not guilty.

37:07.859 --> 37:12.097
I... I can't thank you enough

37:12.197 --> 37:13.765
for believing in me

37:13.865 --> 37:15.867
and for convincing the jury

37:15.967 --> 37:17.936
that that isn't who I am.

37:19.070 --> 37:20.906
I always believed in you.

37:21.006 --> 37:23.108
Thank you.

37:26.645 --> 37:28.614
Ah, and Boatman,

37:28.714 --> 37:32.217
I'm happy to give you every
piece of evidence that I have,

37:32.318 --> 37:33.652
should you want
to build a case

37:33.752 --> 37:35.086
against Volthrupp.

37:35.186 --> 37:36.522
And once we convict,

37:36.622 --> 37:39.658
you'll start up a nice,
juicy class action?

37:39.758 --> 37:40.826
And the woman behind me

37:40.926 --> 37:42.694
will be the first
plaintiff in line.

37:42.794 --> 37:45.331
Send over the files.

37:46.598 --> 37:47.766
Who would have thought

37:47.866 --> 37:49.100
that this
little case that could

37:49.200 --> 37:51.637
would lead to taking
down Big Pharma?

37:51.737 --> 37:52.738
Not you.

37:54.072 --> 37:57.008
Ah. Beautiful.

37:58.910 --> 38:00.346
Oh.

38:00.446 --> 38:01.747
I'm here,
sorry I'm late.

38:01.847 --> 38:03.415
Are you ready?

38:03.515 --> 38:06.117
Yeah, um...

38:06.217 --> 38:07.653
Mom, listen, the letter...

38:07.753 --> 38:09.355
I just, um, I couldn't.

38:09.355 --> 38:11.357
I ju... I-I couldn't,

38:11.457 --> 38:13.158
so I just need you
to tell me what to say.

38:14.192 --> 38:17.128
Oh, so now you do need my help.

38:17.228 --> 38:19.365
Can you, please, just...
It's okay.

38:19.365 --> 38:23.068
I actually did write
a letter for you...

38:24.370 --> 38:26.805
...pointing out...

38:26.905 --> 38:29.074
...that you
are a doctor,

38:29.174 --> 38:31.076
and that you
help people,

38:31.176 --> 38:32.911
and that this event

38:33.011 --> 38:34.946
was a deviation
from the norm.

38:35.046 --> 38:37.115
And...

38:38.917 --> 38:40.386
...something about
how your parents

38:40.386 --> 38:42.421
had very high
expectations for you,

38:42.521 --> 38:44.022
and perhaps

38:44.122 --> 38:46.692
pushed you a bit too hard,

38:46.792 --> 38:49.695
and, in hindsight, regret it.

38:50.462 --> 38:52.664
This sounds like an apology.

38:52.764 --> 38:55.401
That's because it is.

38:56.968 --> 38:58.437
No, no, no. No.

38:58.537 --> 39:01.873
Allison, you
shouldn't go in there

39:01.973 --> 39:04.275
and read
what I wrote.

39:04.410 --> 39:06.311
Isn't that part of the problem?

39:06.412 --> 39:08.046
Isn't that what got us here

39:08.146 --> 39:09.214
in the first place?
What?

39:09.314 --> 39:11.617
Mom, don't rip up...
No, Allison.

39:11.717 --> 39:13.218
It will be fine.

39:13.318 --> 39:14.886
Sweetheart.

39:14.986 --> 39:17.255
You don't need my help.

39:18.089 --> 39:19.458
Allison.

39:19.558 --> 39:23.429
You should go in there
and speak for yourself.

39:24.763 --> 39:26.965
Be yourself.

39:27.065 --> 39:29.535
I'll be right there.

39:29.635 --> 39:31.437
Thank you.

39:32.170 --> 39:33.439
<i>Your Honor,</i>

39:33.539 --> 39:36.442
my client would like
to address the court first.

39:38.243 --> 39:39.878
Uh, thank you,
Your Honor.

39:39.978 --> 39:41.580
I don't quite know what to say.

39:41.680 --> 39:43.348
I, um...

39:43.449 --> 39:45.884
I'm a doctor...

39:45.984 --> 39:47.753
...not that that matters.

39:47.853 --> 39:49.455
But, um...

39:49.555 --> 39:51.723
Well, it kind of matters
because I think

39:51.823 --> 39:53.191
it speaks to my character

39:53.291 --> 39:56.327
that I've made it
my life's work to help people.

39:57.629 --> 39:59.197
But, uh, sorry.
I, um...

39:59.297 --> 40:02.601
I do regret,
very deeply, what happened.

40:02.701 --> 40:06.938
I've never done anything
like that... before.

40:07.038 --> 40:09.274
It was me coloring
outside the lines,

40:09.374 --> 40:12.210
and it went wrong.

40:13.178 --> 40:15.213
I, um...

40:16.515 --> 40:17.816
I don't ever act out.

40:17.916 --> 40:20.686
Not when I'm angry,
not when I'm sad,

40:20.786 --> 40:22.688
not even...

40:22.788 --> 40:24.756
when my dad died...

40:29.461 --> 40:30.762
...when I was 19,

40:30.862 --> 40:33.865
and, you know what,
maybe I should have.

40:33.965 --> 40:35.667
Um...

40:38.403 --> 40:40.839
But, in any event...

40:42.741 --> 40:45.911
I would like to express my...

40:46.011 --> 40:48.113
deep embarrassment and regret

40:48.213 --> 40:49.681
regarding my behavior
that night.

40:49.781 --> 40:52.317
It was a mistake,

40:52.417 --> 40:54.385
and I take responsibility

40:54.486 --> 40:57.255
for my actions.

40:57.355 --> 40:59.290
And...

41:00.291 --> 41:02.160
I would like for you to consider

41:02.260 --> 41:05.564
this honest plea for forgiveness

41:05.664 --> 41:07.332
when considering my sentence.

41:08.634 --> 41:10.101
I hope all of
this sounds like

41:10.201 --> 41:11.302
an apology, because...

41:11.402 --> 41:13.939
it is one.

41:15.440 --> 41:17.676
And how do you plead?

41:17.776 --> 41:21.547
Guilty, Your Honor.
I plead guilty.

41:21.547 --> 41:25.951
I hereby sentence you,
Dr. Allison Grant...

41:27.586 --> 41:30.021
...to 200 hours
community service.

41:30.121 --> 41:31.156
Thank you.

41:45.336 --> 41:46.605
Hi.

41:46.705 --> 41:48.607
Thanks for being here.

41:52.578 --> 41:54.112
This is weird.

41:54.212 --> 41:56.414
To be the responsible one,
to be the reliable one.

41:56.582 --> 41:58.249
Oh, well, let's not get
ahead of ourselves.

41:58.349 --> 41:59.585
I'm just saying,
I'm the good child.

41:59.685 --> 42:00.886
This is what it's like.

42:00.986 --> 42:03.254
I'll give you 72 hours
till you screw it up.

42:03.354 --> 42:05.456
Oh, so Allison's allowed
a departure from the norm

42:05.591 --> 42:06.491
but I'm not?

42:06.592 --> 42:07.593
Well, for Allison,

42:07.693 --> 42:08.694
misbehaving is
the departure.

42:08.794 --> 42:10.829
For you,
it's the norm.

42:11.897 --> 42:14.099
I am sorry, however,
that I assumed

42:14.199 --> 42:16.602
you were
the one arrested.
Yeah, thank you.

42:16.602 --> 42:18.203
Trust me, I'm not getting
collared for some simple

42:18.303 --> 42:19.404
drunk and
disorderly charge.

42:19.504 --> 42:20.839
The next time
I get arrested,

42:20.939 --> 42:22.608
it's gonna be for
something legit... Oh.

42:22.608 --> 42:23.875
...like stealing a boat
or going full vigilante

42:23.975 --> 42:25.611
on some jewel thief.
Right, yes.

42:25.611 --> 42:27.779
Um, I am no longer
representing you in court.

42:27.879 --> 42:29.380
What? No, you can't
get out of it.

42:29.480 --> 42:30.649
You're my mom.

42:30.749 --> 42:32.050
I have you on
permanent retainer.

42:32.150 --> 42:33.451
Oh, you do?

42:33.619 --> 42:34.786
Well, about that,

42:34.886 --> 42:37.455
my price just went up
after this case,

42:37.623 --> 42:39.891
and you can
no longer afford me.

42:41.026 --> 42:44.763
Well, joke's on you.
I could never afford you.

